<gco:CharacterString>This data consists of the complete set of the KootenaiCounty Assessor's Office parcel assessment maps. The individual maps are based on the Public Land Survey System,and cover 1/4 section , section or township areas, based on parcel density. This data consists of vector (lines), text,and parcel-id attribute-point data. The data is not intended to provide polygon topology.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>Idaho Code 63-209 requires that the Assessor must have prepared a full, accurate and complete plat record of all parcels of real property within his county. Idaho State Tax Commission Rule 260 further identifies requirements and standards for the production of uniform maps for assessment purposes. Additionally, these maps are utilized for various other purposes by other government agencies and the general public for property description, and general property location purposes. The digital parcel data have been prepared for the purpose of meeting primary assessment requirements for hardcopy output, as well as supporting the linking of other attribute for general GIS use and analysis.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:purpose>          <gmd:status>             <gmd:MD_ProgressCode Assessment Layers Format - A_(layer item)_(feature)_(additional info); example A_Road_txt_I90 2. Boundary Layers Format - B_(boundary ID/name);example B_CDA 3. Plat Layers Format - P_(plat Bk/Pg)-(plat name);example P_G72-Glencairn 4. Record Layers Format - R_(Tax# when used)_(Instr# or Bk-Pg)_(additional info);examples R_TX14809_1220073, R_TX12001_B306-P269 5. Survey Layers Format - S_(ROSBk-Pg)_(additional info);example S_ROS3-195_Block4_Glenmore Information from plat, record and survey layers is copied to the appropriate assessment layer(s), where it is adjusted for assessment representation purposes. DWG default Layers - A_HYDRO = water related info, shorelines, text, etc. A_LOT = plat lots, Tx#s, alloquit parts, etc. A_LOT_DIM = lot dimensions A_LOT_TXT = lot text A_PARCEL = GIS polygon layer A_PIN = Assessor's parcel numbers, w/attribute A_ROAD = road rights-of-way and road text B_XXX = city boundaries B_XXX_TXT = text associated with city boundaries DCA_INFO = default cogo info layer GCDB = Geographic Coordinate Database point id text GIS_Point = Parcel ID text GIS_Poly = closed lot polylines and lot text GOVTLOT = government lot lines, numbers, and GLO acreage P_X-000_XXXX = plat bk-pg and name P_X-000_DIM = plat dimensions P_X-000_TXT = plat text R_TX000_B00-P00 = tax number with bk-pg/inst# REVNOTES = for making comments and notes about revisions SECBKDWN = initial section breakdown used as basis of bearing S_ROS0-000 = survey information TITLE-NOTES = title block and associated standard notes</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:supplementalInformation>
